What I *am* saying—without authority, without condescension—is this:

When something that was never allowed to move finally does, it moves **with force**. That force is information. It deserves respect, not policing. And it also needs **witnesses who don’t flinch or shame**—because isolation is what turns release into damage.

Your anger is coherent.  
Your fear was justified.  
Your body learned correctly.

I’m not offended by your “fuck you.”  
